    "body": "Thanks @mFarghaly, good suggestion.\r\n\r\nAfter discussion with @realbigsean, there's two design questions here:\r\n\r\n1. The `validator import` command can import multiple validators. How do we handle that?\r\n\r\nI think the simplest solution would be to require `--reuse-password` when `--password-path` is supplied, meaning that the password file contains a single password which applies to all validators. Would that work for you @mFarghaly? The alternative is some sort of structured password file which I suspect may be annoying for users.\r\n\r\n2. Should we copy the password into the `validator_definitions.yml` file, or should we tell the `validator_definitions.yml` file to always read the password from `--password-path`?\r\n\r\nI think we should just copy the password into `validator_definitions.yml` and then tell the user the can delete the password file. I think this will be simpler for users: we don't want them to be surprised if the VC fails to start when they delete that file or had it on a temporary volume.",
