    "body": "\r\n\r\n> I think the simplest solution would be to require --reuse-password when --password-path is supplied\r\n\r\nThis works!\r\n\r\nAnother approach is `--password-path` can be used only with `--keystore` option to import a single keystone at a time. In other words `--password-path` can't be used with `--directory` option.\r\n\r\n\r\n> Should we copy the password into the validator_definitions.yml file, or should we tell the validator_definitions.yml file to always read the password from --password-path?\r\n\r\nPrioritizing security here, I prefer reading password content from password path, or copying the file to `{data dir}/secrets/{validator public key}` to make sure it won't cause an issue if user accidentally deletes the file.\r\n",
